90 ANALYsm.

Devastations of Marcellus in Samnium. Samnites ap- peal to Hannibal for aid. His reply. He and Hanno (ex Bruttiis) summon Nola to surrender. Answer of Herennius Bassus. Attack on the place repulsed with loss. Hannibal retires into Apulia, and the campaign ends without anything more of importance in Italy, (xlii—xlviii.)

SPAIN. Demand of the Scipios for supplies. Debate in the senate, and resolutions. Siege of Iliturgis by the Carthaginian leaders raised by Scipio. Revolt of Spanish tribes to the Romans, (xlviii.‚ xlix.)
